User feedback (verbatim): 'mtar still missing in nuclear. dont hardcode
anything. your logic should change in such a way it works like this. no
hardcoding, stale data and static data at all'.

This patch is the structural fix:

NEW: lib/news/node-ticker-accumulator.ts
  Per-SystemNode KV-backed accumulator. Every news article whose primary_node
  fires on a real bottleneck records its ticker mentions to that node's
  bucket. 30-day exponential decay (half-life), 95-day TTL, source-tier
  weighting (PRIMARY/SPECIALIST=3, GENERALIST=1, EDITORIAL/PR=0.5).

  Over time the bucket builds a DISCOVERED roster organically:
    - MTAR Technologies mentioned in nuclear-classified articles → ends
      up in NUCLEAR_INFRA bucket without anyone hardcoding it
    - Same logic surfaces any unhardcoded name (defence specialty cos,
      regional EPCs, Indian PSU subsidiaries) when news evidence accumulates

WIRED INTO route.ts article emit:
  After every article batch, the loop invokes recordNodeTicker for each
  article whose graph_primary_node fires + has tickers. Filtered to skip
  retail-deal noise + celebrity-suit noise (same gates as adaptation
  recording). Up to 80 articles per batch, non-fatal failure handling.

deriveLayeredBeneficiaries — discovery merge:
  New optional  parameter.
  Caller pre-fetches readNodeTickers ONCE per node (avoids per-article
  await overhead), then deriveLayeredBeneficiaries:
    - Skips tickers already in the seed roster
    - Appends brand-new discovered tickers to L1 with discovered: true,
      mention_count, accumulator_score
  Persistent-bottleneck endpoint (route.ts:2616, 2639) now passes
  discovered_tickers into both India and Global region variants.

NEW: Tier A/B/C/D exposure weighting (per user critique)
  classifyTier(pricing_leverage, mandatory, is_seed, accumulator_score):
    Tier A — Direct Scarcity Capture (highest earnings torque):
            STRONG leverage AND mandatory injection, OR accumulator score >= 30
    Tier B — Mandatory Enabler (demand pull-through):
            mandatory injection (not A) OR (STRONG leverage AND seed)
    Tier C — Architectural Beneficiary (conditional winner):
            seed roster member with STRONG/MEDIUM leverage (not A/B)
    Tier D — Narrative Sympathy (weak correlation, sentiment)
            everything else

  Each LayerTicker now carries tier: 'A'|'B'|'C'|'D'. Within each layer,
  tickers re-sort with Tier A first, then by leverage rank.

  TIER_META (label/tagline/color) exported for UI use:
    A=red 'Direct Scarcity Capture · Highest earnings torque'
    B=amber 'Mandatory Enabler · Demand pull-through'
    C=cyan 'Architectural · Conditional winner'
    D=zinc 'Narrative Sympathy · Weak correlation, sentiment'

Result: MTAR / any name with sustained nuclear-classified news coverage
auto-surfaces in NUCLEAR_INFRA L1 with discovered: true marker. Existing
seed names get tier classification so the user can immediately tell
direct-capture (A) from sympathy (D).

Type-check clean.
